OL,6,F"Irrespective of Mills inevitably
OL,7,Fbeing dismissed, given he is rightly
OL,8,Fcurrently serving a prison sentence as
OL,9,Fa convicted sex offender, it was
OL,10,Fimportant we still hold these
OL,11,Fproceedings to ensure he is not only
OL,12,Fdismissed from GMP but also placed on
OL,13,Fthe barred list
OL,15,F"Mills will never work in law
OL,16,Fenforcement again.
